  247. ‌let set_int_arg round (arg:Int_arg_helper.parsed ref) default value =
  248.   let value : int =
  249.     match value with
  250.     | None -> default
  251.     | Some value -> value
  252.   in
  253.   match round with
  254.   | None ->
  255.     arg := Int_arg_helper.set_base_default value
  256. ‌             (Int_arg_helper.reset_base_overrides !arg)
  257.   | Some round ->
  258.     arg := Int_arg_helper.add_base_override round value !arg

  260. let set_float_arg round (arg:Float_arg_helper.parsed ref) default value =

  357. let all_passes = ref []
  358. let dumped_passes_list = ref []
  359. let dumped_pass s =
  360.   assert(List.mem s !all_passes);
  361.   List.mem s !dumped_passes_list

  363. let set_dumped_pass s enabled =
  364.   if (List.mem s !all_passes) then begin
  365.     let passes_without_s = List.filter ((<>) s) !dumped_passes_list in
  366.     let dumped_passes =
  367.       if enabled then
  368.         s :: passes_without_s
  369.       else
  370.         passes_without_s
  371.     in
  372.     dumped_passes_list := dumped_passes
  373.   end

  428.       | Linear -> "linear"
  429.     in
  430.     ".cmir-" ^ ext

  432.   (** [extract_extension_with_pass filename] returns the IR whose extension
  433.       is a prefix of the extension of [filename], and the suffix,
  434.       which can be used to distinguish different passes on the same IR.
  435.       For example, [extract_extension_with_pass "foo.cmir-linear123"]
  436.       returns [Some (Linear, "123")]. *)
  437.   let extract_extension_with_pass filename =
  438.     let ext = Filename.extension filename in
  439.     let ext_len = String.length ext in
  440.     if ext_len <= 0 then None
  441.     else begin
  442.       let is_prefix ir =
  443.         let s = extension ir in
  444.         let s_len = String.length s in
  445.         s_len <= ext_len && s = String.sub ext 0 s_len
  446.       in
  447.       let drop_prefix ir =
  448.         let s = extension ir in
  449.         let s_len = String.length s in
  450.         String.sub ext s_len (ext_len - s_len)
  451.       in
  452.       let ir = List.find_opt is_prefix all in
  453.       match ir with
  454.       | None -> None
  455.       | Some ir -> Some (ir, drop_prefix ir)
  456.     end
  457. end

  459. (* This is used by the -stop-after option. *)
  460. module Compiler_pass = struct
  461.   (* If you add a new pass, the following must be updated:
  462.      - the variable `passes` below
  463.      - the manpages in man/ocaml{c,opt}.m
  464.      - the manual manual/src/cmds/unified-options.etex
  465.   *)
  466.   type t = Parsing | Typing | Lambda | Scheduling | Emit

  468.   let to_string = function
  469.     | Parsing -> "parsing"
  470.     | Typing -> "typing"
  471.     | Lambda -> "lambda"
  472.     | Scheduling -> "scheduling"
  473.     | Emit -> "emit"

  475.   let of_string = function
  476.     | "parsing" -> Some Parsing
  477.     | "typing" -> Some Typing
  478.     | "lambda" -> Some Lambda
  479.     | "scheduling" -> Some Scheduling
  480.     | "emit" -> Some Emit
  481.     | _ -> None

  483.   let rank = function
  484.     | Parsing -> 0
  485.     | Typing -> 1
  486.     | Lambda -> 2
  487.     | Scheduling -> 50
  488.     | Emit -> 60

  490.   let passes = [
  491.     Parsing;
  492.     Typing;
  493.     Lambda;
  494.     Scheduling;
  495.     Emit;
  496.   ]
  497.   let is_compilation_pass _ = true
  498.   let is_native_only = function
  499.     | Scheduling -> true
  500.     | Emit -> true
  501.     | _ -> false

  503.   let enabled is_native t = not (is_native_only t) || is_native
  504.   let can_save_ir_after = function
  505.     | Scheduling -> true
  506.     | _ -> false

  508.   let available_pass_names ~filter ~native =
  509.     passes
  510.     |> List.filter (enabled native)
  511.     |> List.filter filter
  512.     |> List.map to_string

  514.   let compare a b =
  515.     compare (rank a) (rank b)

  517.   let to_output_filename t ~prefix =
  518.     match t with
  519.     | Scheduling -> prefix ^ Compiler_ir.(extension Linear)
  520.     | _ -> Misc.fatal_error "Not supported"

  522.   let of_input_filename name =
  523.     match Compiler_ir.extract_extension_with_pass name with
  524.     | Some (Linear, _) -> Some Emit
  525.     | None -> None
  526. end

  528. ‌let stop_after = ref None (* -stop-after *)

  530. ‌let should_stop_after pass =
  531.   if Compiler_pass.(rank Typing <= rank pass) && !print_types then true
  532.   else
  533.     match !stop_after with
  534.     | None -> false
  535.     | Some stop -> Compiler_pass.rank stop <= Compiler_pass.rank pass

  537. ‌let save_ir_after = ref []

  539. ‌let should_save_ir_after pass =
  540.   List.mem pass !save_ir_after

  542. ‌let set_save_ir_after pass enabled =
  543.   let other_passes = List.filter ((<>) pass) !save_ir_after in
  544.   let new_passes =
  545.     if enabled then
  546.       pass :: other_passes
  547.     else
  548.       other_passes
  549.   in

  552. module String = Misc.Stdlib.String

  554. let arg_spec = ref []
  555. let arg_names = ref String.Map.empty

  557. let reset_arguments () =
  558.   arg_spec := [];
  559.   arg_names := String.Map.empty

  561. let add_arguments loc args =
  562.   List.iter (function (arg_name, _, _) as arg ->
  563.     try
  564.       let loc2 = String.Map.find arg_name !arg_names in
  565.       Printf.eprintf
  566.         "Warning: compiler argument %s is already defined:\n" arg_name;
  567.       Printf.eprintf "   First definition: %s\n" loc2;
  568.       Printf.eprintf "   New definition: %s\n" loc;
  569.     with Not_found ->
  570.       arg_spec := !arg_spec @ [ arg ];
  571.       arg_names := String.Map.add arg_name loc !arg_names
  572.   ) args

  574. let create_usage_msg program =
  575.   Printf.sprintf "Usage: %s <options> <files>\n\
  576.     Try '%s --help' for more information." program program


  579. let print_arguments program =
  580.   Arg.usage !arg_spec (create_usage_msg program)
